cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper proposes new benchmark reinforcement learning domains that aim to capture some of the complexity of the natural world. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on reinforcement learning and evaluation of algorithms, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
